---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { site } from '../lib/site';

const pillars = [
  'real race-car context before catalog theory',
  'density-altitude thinking as the niche moat',
  'guides and builds as the trust layer behind commerce',
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Stroom Performance"
  description="Stroom Performance started on YouTube, wrenching on a real high-altitude drag car. The store exists to sell the parts that actually work where the air runs thin."
>
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="wrap about-hero__wrap">
      <div class="about-hero__copy">
        <Breadcrumb crumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'About' }]} />
        <p class="label-small accent reveal">About Stroom</p>
        <h1 class="heading-section about-hero__title reveal">Built on the runs, not a catalog.</h1>
        <p class="muted about-hero__body reveal">
          Stroom starts with a real car, a real channel, and a real high-altitude
          problem set. The store exists because generic performance shops do not
          answer the questions that actually matter when the air runs thin.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="about-hero__sidebar reveal">
        <p class="about-hero__sidebar-label">Operating pillars</p>
        <div class="about-hero__sidebar-rule"></div>
        <ul class="about-hero__sidebar-list">
          {pillars.map((pillar) => <li>{pillar}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-story">
    <div class="wrap about-story__wrap">
      <div class="about-story__intro reveal">
        <p class="label-small accent">Why It Exists</p>
        <h2 class="heading-section">A specialist store makes more sense than pretending altitude does not matter.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-story__body reveal">
        <p>
          Stroom Performance started where a lot of good racing knowledge
          starts: on the car, in the garage, and on the internet. Cutting access
          panels to service a fuel pump. Chasing a converter that flashes where
          it should at altitude. Reading data logs to understand why a pass went
          sideways on an un-prepped lane.
        </p>
        <p>
          That is the reason the store exists. Most performance shops assume sea
          level. Stroom does not. High density altitude changes the engine, the
          fuel math, the converter behavior, and the margin for error. The
          future catalog is supposed to reflect those realities, not ignore
          them.
        </p>
        <p>
          The site is being built in stages. Guides and builds carry the
          expertise now while the product assortment grows. The throughline stays
          the same: show the judgment first, then make the right parts easier to buy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-cta">
    <div class="wrap about-cta__panel reveal">
      <div>
        <p class="label-small accent">What To Do Next</p>
        <h2 class="heading-section">Watch the work, read the guides, or find the right part.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-cta__actions">
        <a href={site.youtube} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-outline">Watch the Channel</a>
        <a href="/guides" class="btn-outline">Read the Guides</a>
        <a href="/shop" class="btn-primary">Shop Parts</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
